---
/**
 * /insights → 308 https://web.plyaz.net/en/blog
 *
 * Hard SSR endpoint (`prerender = false`) — Astro builds this as a
 * Vercel serverless function instead of a static HTML page. The
 * function returns a real HTTP 308 with a Location header, so the
 * browser performs the redirect instantly at the edge instead of
 * loading a meta-refresh shim.
 *
 * Why not vercel.json: Vercel ignores root vercel.json redirects
 * when the framework uses the Build Output API (the @astrojs/vercel
 * adapter does). Probe confirmed: a sentinel rule in vercel.json
 * still 404s on prod. The adapter's own redirect map doesn't accept
 * `[...slug]` sources (build fails on GetStaticPathsRequired), so
 * SSR pages are the only path that produces real edge 308s.
 *
 * Locale prefix `/en/` is baked in so the browser never hops through
 * the webapp's `/blog` → `/en/blog` 307.
 */
export const prerender = false;
return Astro.redirect('https://web.plyaz.net/en/blog', 308);
---
